<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="316" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,320,1102]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1004,1030]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mahmood, 1967" authorityName="Mahmood" authorityYear="1967" box="[606,921,1004,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Singapora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[606,723,1005,1031]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="316">Singapora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mahmood, S. H." box="[731,921,1004,1030]" pageId="15" pageNumber="316" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref33859" refString="Mahmood, S. H. (1967) A study of the typhlocybine genera of the Oriental region (Thailand, the Philippines and adjoining areas). Pacific Insects Monograph, 12, 1 - 52." type="journal article" year="1967">Mahmood, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the vertex lacks a dark spot apically, the ocelli are rudimentary, the subgenital plate lacks marginal macrosetae subbasally, the style is shorter and the aedeagal shaft is fused with the preatrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
